org.dgfoundation.amp.nireports

Class TranslatedDate

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.dgfoundation.amp.nireports.TranslatedDate
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable<TranslatedDate>

    public class TranslatedDate
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Comparable<TranslatedDate>
    a class which is used for stored the result of translating a LocalDate into some schema-specific calendar and then stripping the "day of month" part Calendars can inflict any type of change to a date, including:
    • renaming months
    • shifting months (so that, for example, September is the first month of the year)
    • have years with a non-12 number-of-months
    • have years with a "non-number number". For example FY 2013/2014 is a valid year name in certain calendars
    . Thus, the generic encoding of a year translated into any calendar is as follows:
    A TranslatedDate has 3 parts: year, quarter and month. Each of these is a ComparableValue, thus both arbitrary ordering and arbitrary displaying is supported.
    A total ordering is achieved by sorting on the 3-tuple (year, quarter, month). 2 instances are considered equal iff the result of comparing them returns 0.
